    "updated_at": "2013-09-22T17:57:08Z",
    "body": "It shouldn't silently fail to work if there are non-UTF-8 file paths. Assuming all paths can be stored in strings is incorrect on Rust's part. It's not true on Windows either, because NTFS uses UCS2 and doesn't enforce valid Unicode.\n",
